 :tx/rationale "AMBIENT RECONCILIATION — VERIFICATION AND COMPOUNDING: Verification has 3 layers. (1) Proptest: for any entity E with spec refs R, spec_graph_neighbors(store, R) returns only entities that share at least one ref in R (no false positives). (2) Regression test: create store with ACP EPIC (traces to INV-INTERFACE-001) and TSV task (traces to INV-INTERFACE-001). Run braid task create for TSV. Verify :recon/trace datom includes ACP EPIC. This is the EXACT failure mode that triggered this analysis. (3) E2E script: e2e_ambient_reconciliation.sh — create spec elements, tasks tracing to them, run 5 commands in same neighborhood, verify braid status shows concentration warning. Compounding: every command adds a trace datom. After 100 commands per session × 30 sessions = 3000 trace datoms. The concentration detector has full visibility into which spec neighborhoods are hot. This is the self-improvement loop (SEED.md S7) applied to reconciliation — the system learns which areas of the spec are being actively worked on and surfaces connections automatically. The trace data also feeds the R(t) routing system: tasks in concentrated neighborhoods get a contention_boost because the agent is already in that conceptual space."
